</span>
</p>
<p class='talk-transcript__para'>
<data class='talk-transcript__para__time'>
 4:52
</data>
<span class='talk-transcript__para__text'>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='281000' id='t-281000'>Now I'm a big fan of commitment devices actually.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='284000' id='t-284000'>Tying yourself to the mast is the oldest one, but there are other ones</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='287000' id='t-287000'>such as locking a credit card away with a key</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='291000' id='t-291000'>or not bringing junk food into the house so you won't eat it</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='294000' id='t-294000'>or unplugging your Internet connection</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='296000' id='t-296000'>so you can use your computer.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='298000' id='t-298000'>I was creating commitment devices of my own</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='300000' id='t-300000'>long before I knew what they were.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='302000' id='t-302000'>So when I was a starving post-doc</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='304000' id='t-304000'>at Columbia University,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='306000' id='t-306000'>I was deep in a publish-or-perish phase of my career.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='309000' id='t-309000'>I had to write five pages a day</span>
