</span>
</p>
<p class='talk-transcript__para'>
<data class='talk-transcript__para__time'>
 7:33
</data>
<span class='talk-transcript__para__text'>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='442000' id='t-442000'>So I've been working</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='444000' id='t-444000'>for about a decade now</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='446000' id='t-446000'>on finding other ways</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='448000' id='t-448000'>to change people's relationship to the future self</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='450000' id='t-450000'>without using commitment devices.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='452000' id='t-452000'>In particular, I'm interested in the relationship</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='455000' id='t-455000'>to the future financial self.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='459000' id='t-459000'>And this is a timely issue.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='461000' id='t-461000'>I'm talking about the topic of saving.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='463000' id='t-463000'>Now saving is a classic two selves problem.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='465000' id='t-465000'>The present self does not want to save at all.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='468000' id='t-468000'>It wants to consume.</span>
